---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead
			title="Privacy Policy — Little Wonder Care"
			description="How Little Wonder Care collects, uses, and protects your personal information."
		/>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />

		<main>

			<!-- Page Hero -->
			<div class="page-hero bg-crema">
				<p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
				<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
				<p class="subtitle">Last updated: April 2026</p>
			</div>

			<!-- Prose Content -->
			<div class="section">
				<div class="privacy-prose">

					<p class="privacy-intro">
						Your privacy matters to me. This policy explains what information I collect when you use Little Wonder Care's website or services, how I use it, and your rights around it. I've written it in plain English because legal jargon helps no one.
					</p>

					<div class="privacy-section">
						<h2>Information I Collect</h2>
						<p>I only collect information you actively give me. This includes:</p>
						<ul>
							<li><strong>Contact forms</strong> — your name, email address, and any message you send through this site.</li>
							<li><strong>Booking forms</strong> — your name, email, phone number, due date, and any details you share when requesting a service or scheduling a call.</li>
							<li><strong>Email sign-ups</strong> — your email address if you subscribe to receive guides, tips, or newsletters.</li>
						</ul>
						<p>I don't collect any information without your knowledge, and I never buy or sell contact lists.</p>
					</div>

					<div class="privacy-section">
						<h2>How I Use Your Information</h2>
						<p>The information you share with me is used to:</p>
						<ul>
							<li>Respond to your questions and inquiries</li>
							<li>Deliver the services you've booked or requested</li>
							<li>Send you resources, guides, or updates you've signed up for</li>
							<li>Improve this website and my offerings over time</li>
						</ul>
						<p>I will never sell your personal information to third parties, and I only share it with service providers who help me run my business (see below).</p>
					</div>

					<div class="privacy-section">
						<h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
						<p>I use a small number of trusted third-party tools to run this website and my services. Each of these processes your data according to their own privacy policies, which I encourage you to review:</p>
						<ul>
							<li><strong>Formspree</strong> — handles contact form submissions and routes messages to my inbox.</li>
							<li><strong>Cal.com</strong> — powers the scheduling and booking system for consultations and discovery calls.</li>
							<li><strong>Stripe</strong> — processes payments securely. I never see or store your payment card details.</li>
							<li><strong>Kit (formerly ConvertKit)</strong> — manages email subscribers and sends newsletters or guides you've opted into.</li>
							<li><strong>Analytics</strong> — I may use privacy-friendly analytics (such as Vercel Analytics) to understand how visitors use the site. No personally identifiable data is collected for this purpose.</li>
						</ul>
					</div>

					<div class="privacy-section">
						<h2>Cookies</h2>
						<p>This site uses minimal cookies. I do not use advertising cookies or tracking cookies for cross-site behavioral profiling. Any cookies in use are either essential for the site to function or used for basic, anonymized analytics to understand how the site is being used.</p>
						<p>You can disable cookies in your browser settings at any time without affecting your ability to use this site.</p>
					</div>

					<div class="privacy-section">
						<h2>Data Security</h2>
						<p>I take reasonable measures to protect your information. This site is served over HTTPS (SSL encryption), and the third-party services I use (Stripe, Cal.com, Kit) are industry-standard platforms with their own robust security practices.</p>
						<p>No method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure, but I'm committed to handling your data responsibly and only keeping it as long as necessary.</p>
					</div>

					<div class="privacy-section">
						<h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
						<p>My services are designed to support parents and families — I absolutely love working with families who have little ones! However, this website is not directed at children under the age of 13, and I do not knowingly collect personal information from anyone under 13. If you believe a child has submitted information through this site, please contact me and I'll remove it promptly.</p>
					</div>

					<div class="privacy-section">
						<h2>Your Rights</h2>
						<p>You have the right to:</p>
						<ul>
							<li><strong>Access</strong> the personal information I hold about you</li>
							<li><strong>Correct</strong> any information that is inaccurate</li>
							<li><strong>Request deletion</strong> of your personal information</li>
							<li><strong>Unsubscribe</strong> from email communications at any time (every email includes an unsubscribe link)</li>
						</ul>
						<p>To exercise any of these rights, just send me an email at <a href="mailto:hello@littlewondercare.com">hello@littlewondercare.com</a> and I'll take care of it.</p>
					</div>

					<div class="privacy-section">
						<h2>Contact</h2>
						<p>If you have any questions about this privacy policy or how your data is handled, please reach out:</p>
						<p>
							<strong>Little Wonder Care</strong><br />
							Email: <a href="mailto:hello@littlewondercare.com">hello@littlewondercare.com</a><br />
							Waco, TX
						</p>
					</div>

					<div class="privacy-section">
						<h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
						<p>I may update this policy from time to time as my services or tools change. When I do, I'll update the "Last updated" date at the top of this page. I encourage you to check back occasionally, but I'll only make changes that are reasonable and in keeping with the spirit of this policy.</p>
						<p>Continuing to use this site after any changes means you accept the updated policy.</p>
					</div>

				</div>
			</div>

		</main>

		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	main { width: 100%; max-width: 100%; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

	.privacy-prose {
		max-width: 720px;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	.privacy-intro {
		font-size: 1.05rem;
		line-height: 1.8;
		color: rgba(45, 45, 45, 0.8);
		font-style: italic;
		padding-bottom: 40px;
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(183, 201, 206, 0.35);
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.privacy-section {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.privacy-section h2 {
		font-family: var(--font-serif);
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: var(--teal-scuro);
		margin-bottom: 16px;
		padding-bottom: 10px;
		border-bottom: 2px solid rgba(183, 201, 206, 0.4);
	}

	.privacy-section p {
		font-size: 0.97rem;
		line-height: 1.8;
		color: rgba(45, 45, 45, 0.78);
		margin-bottom: 14px;
	}

	.privacy-section p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

	.privacy-section ul {
		margin: 12px 0 16px 0;
		padding: 0;
		list-style: none;
	}

	.privacy-section ul li {
		font-size: 0.97rem;
		line-height: 1.7;
		color: rgba(45, 45, 45, 0.78);
		padding: 6px 0 6px 24px;
		position: relative;
	}

	.privacy-section ul li::before {
		content: '→';
		position: absolute;
		left: 0;
		color: var(--corallo);
		font-size: 0.85rem;
	}

	.privacy-section a {
		color: var(--corallo);
		font-weight: 500;
	}

	.privacy-section a:hover { color: var(--pesca); }
</style>
